    <note type="biography">
        <p>British politician and writer. Son of George Douglas Campbell, eighth duke of Argyll. MP for Argyllshire, 1868–78. Married Queen Victoria’s fourth daughter, Louise, in 1871. Governor-general of Canada, 1878–83. Wrote works of travel and biography. Assumed the courtesy title marquess of Lorne in 1847; became ninth duke of Argyll in 1900, but continued to be widely known as marquess of Lorne.
        </p></note>
